## The All-in-One Question

HockeyStack bundles attribution + web analytics + surveys. Is that what you want?

```
All-in-One (HockeyStack):
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Pros:
├── Single vendor
├── Pre-integrated data
├── Faster deployment
└── Unified interface

Cons:
├── Paying for features you may not need
├── Not best-in-class at each component
├── Harder to swap pieces
└── Vendor lock-in


Best-of-Breed (mbuzz + other tools):
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Pros:
├── Best tool for each job
├── Swap components as needed
├── Pay only for what you need
└── Deep expertise per area

Cons:
├── More vendors to manage
├── Integration work required
├── Potentially longer setup
└── Data stitching needed
```

If you already have web analytics (GA4, Heap, Amplitude), HockeyStack's bundled analytics is redundant cost.

